review_blob: Nice aroma of cereals and yeast. Lovely appearance directly after pouring, with a consistent foam. Taste unfortunately a bit watery, but nice notes of caramel, malt, no bitterness, coffee. Leave chocolate aftertones in mouth. Nice surprise.
A weird smell of tenderized meat. Very strong but not bitter at all: like a good porto. Lovely reddish color. Not my kind of beer but a very good representant of the barley wine category.

I was in awe when I poured it. Its magic, like a snowball. Smells of clove, hot wine, walnuts. Opaque with almost no foam. Quite bland on the tongue: taste of cereals, biscuit and raisins but disappears quickly.

If you like smoked herrings, thats for you. Its not really my type of beer, but thats fun. Delicate, but thats a whole meal, heh. Smells real good. Dont mix with other beers as you will get the smoke blocked in your throat for long.

Cloudy yellow color, very beautiful consistant foam. Smells of quinces, alcohol and hops. Bitter first taste which gets more balanced afterwards. No real particular taste, you get warm from the alcohol but thats all.
Taste of watery pears and malt. Doesnt smell much. Nice yellow color. Forgettable, unfortunately.

Floral aroma, rose notes. Although its only 4.5%, you smell the alcohol. Golden color, a little inconsistant foam, no laces. A few bubbles. Taste of white bread, great balance in tastes but no particular pike in the tastes either. Quickly disappear in mouth. Lacks character, but good nonetheless.

Deep orange color with lots of foam, giving incredible laces. Smells of clove and orange, candycane and almonds. Frank bitterness in mouth with a lovely aftertaste of almonds, a bit sugary but not too much. The balance is remarquable. For English speakers, the name translates to the redhead farts and is a wordplay on rouspter which means to grumble.
beer_name: Bire de lOurcq La Rousse Pete

review_blob: Strong cocoa, almond, nuts aroma. Golden color with very beautiful foam. Round taste, strong with very bitter aftertaste.

Golden color with consistant foam. Smell of grapefruit and malt. A bit too watery, a higher carbonation would be nice. Still, it would great on tap. Great complexity on the palate with a nice bitter aftertaste. A session IPA that I could drink all night without any problem.
You do smell the very high alcohol. Weirdly, it seems of cherries. Taste of red fruits: cherries, raspberries, and roses. Alcohol and coffee. Very nice and quickly drunk.

Its like a snow ball when you have it in your glass. Smells of herbs, rice, fish. Taste of rice of course, sugary, balanced with a bit of saltiness. Incredible sensation on the palate - coats your entire throat with a very interesting sugary taste. And look at that cover!

Orange color with a little foam, disappears quickly. Smells of bread, caramel and nuts. Very malty, sugary with a bitter aftertaste. Surprising but not very pleasant. Not balanced. Fun but not of my likings.

Very beautiful color. Slightly acid. Smells of raspberry and lemon. Interesting Berliner Weisse but I dont really think the raspberry is a gimmick more than a feature. Could be added as a syrup. Not really worth the 13? I paid.

Very nice golden color with plenty of consistent foam. Faint malts aroma. Nice malty taste, bitter but very balanced, round with hints of clove and licorice. Doesnt stay much on the palate. Could be treacherous: very easily swallowed, but 8%. Would be great on tap and very cold.

This beer is beautiful. Cloudy with lots of foam, coming down like a magma lamp. Pale golden color. First taste is heaven, you can clearly define several parts in the beer hitting your mouth, tongue, palate, transforming them selves within seconds. Floral aroma with hints of clove, subtle. Taste round at first then strongly bitter, and a nearly sugary finish that leaves a great impression on the palate. High class beer.
Blindfolded, I could easily think its a gose! A delicacy, with aromas of pear and salt. Light color like a white wine. Spiky! Will definitely drink again.
A bit of a deception actually. Clear and golden color, but s chemical aftertaste that transform the Salvia taste strangely. And no salt in view...

A bit watery (indeed a session IPA), but a very beautiful color and average taste. Hops, caramel, flowers in the front taste and toasted cereal aftertaste. You will have several but you will forget it easily.

Almost tar, creamy foam appearance, with visible carbonation. Coffee, chocolate and toasted bread aroma, floral hints. Salty taste, like a good fish. Very good balance between bitterness, sourness and the rest. Strong malts, but still not throwing the rest unbalanced. Burnt wood and malty aftertates, very pleasant. Four stars! Really liked it during winter.
beer_name: De la Senne Brusseleir Zwet IPA

review_blob: The color of the label is the color of the beer in the light. Very beautiful foam. Smells of mango and berries, perhaps a bit of raisins. Wonderful taste of hops, raisins, just balanced between sugary and smoky. A bit bitter on the palate afterwards but thats not unpleasant. Very full-bodied. A great one that I will certainly keep in my favorites.
Doesnt smell much. Very fresh, very floral. The floral taste of hibiscus stays on the tongue for a long time but theres not much more to that beer. Not bad though, very special.

beer_brewer_name: Les Brasseurs du Grand Paris (My Beer Company)
review_blob: Reasonable aroma of mango. Lovely color with just enough foam. Taste of roses. Highly drinkable. A very typical IPA.
beer_name: Les Brasseurs du Grand Paris La Levalloise (>2012)

review_blob: Dark brown with almost no foam. Creamy but very syrupy (if thats a word). Almost no aroma. Very roasty, burnt wood taste. Hints of coffee. So much sugar! Its almost like cough drop. Cant say I liked it.

I smell the sea, salt, lime! What an unusual combination. Pale yellow, cloudy, with a lot of foam (like the north sea). The taste is acidic, not bitter, salty of course and a bit of lemon. Stay on the palate a longue time like a citric candy. Very unusual and a lovely combination. I had memories of the North Sea coming back suddenly. Emotional beer!

Deep amber colour with a good amount of consistent foam. Faint aroma of berries. Great taste of raisins, malt and sugary treats, great balance. Treacherous, it good down very well and very quick I loved it, will have more and buy it to friends. The design of the bottle itself is sufficient to give it a go.
Very unusual, but I couldnt finish even my glass because of the bitterness that took my mouth by surprise. Ouch.

Troubled cider apparence, nearly no foam. A delicate aroma of quince and pear. Taste is tart, yellow fruit, rhubarb and flowers, lightly acid, vivid, a pleasure. Stay on the tongue with no bitterness. Id like to drink this on tap! My first gose and certainly already a fan of the style...

Beautiful aspect, trouble golden with lovely carbonation. Great mango and berries aroma. The taste is quite off-putting as it is very bitter and the bitterness stays on the palate... Without these mango aftertones. Disappointed by the unbalance.

Very unusual heavy feeling on the tongue with this strong IPA. The aroma is a trick: fruity, light, unsuspicious. Then its very oily with smoky and woody tastes - leather aftertones. A bit too much sometimes but the name should tell its not for everyone, its a "heavy metal" double IPA! Great color and opacity. Stays well on the tongue.
beer_name: La Valle de Chevreuse Rotten Skull American IPA

review_blob: Wonderful aroma, litchi, pines, sandalwood. Lovely color and a soft yet consistent foam. The taste is not too bitter, not too sweet. Very balanced, delicate but great on the palate. I really love the wood aftertones. Im very proud to say its produced just near my place, will visit them!

33cl in bottle. Flowery aroma, strong and pleasant. Lot of foam, very nice amber color, a bit opaque for a blonde. Strikenly bitter, salty like good fish, hops finish. Leave a bitter taste in the mouth which is not unpleasant. It says its a "popular" one but I find this beer very "posh" on the contrary.

33 in bottle. Very subtile aroma - nuts, roasty. Very light, changing very fast. The color is lovely : deep amber, opaque. At opening, beautiful foam but not consistant, totally gone after three minutes - I consider this a feature! You dont really taste any raisins in the beer. Theres an strange but pleasant aftertaste reminding me of the green syrup they put in beer in Germany. Lovely! Great balance and it the slight bitterness it leaves on the tongue is great. Oh: have you seen the packaging? Wow.

beer_brewer_name: Brasserie des Sources (formerly: de St. Amand)
review_blob: Pungent litchi aroma, also very present in the taste - a bit too much, destroying all around it, although you can taste a bit of berries in the back. More on the side of IPA than bire de Garde. The palate is fizzy and very nice. A bit of foam with nice laces. In globality a refreshing one, balanced. Would like to try it on tap.

Discreet alcohol and sugar aroma, quite delicate. Apparence is common, without much bubbles nor foam, golden. Taste a bit salty, very balanced. Very light palate, a bit fizzy, numbing. A strong one, you know it from the start, but a solid one.

Very thin grassy aroma. A lovely golden color with soft bubbles, balanced foam in a pilsner glass. Poor taste, wheaty water, but a very agreable palate. I would drink that while eating, so it doesnt taint my food.
In 500 mL can. Plastic, yeast and nothing else. Oh well, when you want to get drunk and youre thirsty...

Smoky aromas, wood tones but a bit dry, lacks complexity. Very lovely foam, consistent. Not bitter at all, slightly sour but not in a bad way. Very balanced. Doesnt appear to be 8% - very treacherous.
The rose aroma is thick but the bitterness was a bit too much. Whatever, I really liked it, its very refreshing and a great taste.
